criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          1. Right-handed females 18-55 years of age (TMDs are more prevalent in females);

          2. diagnosed with muscle pain disorders as classified by the new Diagnostic Criteria for
             Temporomandibular Disorders (DC/TMD);

          3. have had pain in the masticatory muscle for at least 3 months;

          4. have chronic masticatory muscle pain not attributable to recent acute trauma, previous
             infection, or active inflammation; and

          5. have a moderate or severe baseline pain score of 30 mm or greater using a 100 mm VAS.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. Metabolic, rheumatoid, or vascular diseases;

          2. commonly comorbid functional chronic pain disorders (e.g., irritable bowel syndrome,
             fibromyalgia);

          3. psychiatric disorders (e.g., depression, schizophrenia, attention deficit
             hyperactivity disorder);

          4. abnormal neurological examination;

          5. contraindication for MRI scanning (e.g., metallic surgical implant);

          6. self-report of substance abuse;

          7. exercise therapy in the 6 months before entry into the study or current treatment for
             TMD;

          8. previous experience with electrotherapy; or

          9. pregnant or planning a pregnancy.

        After confirming eligibility to participate in the study, all participants will be asked to
        sign an informed consent in accordance with the UofA´s policies on research using human
        participants.
